# .dockerignore — keeps the Docker build context small and clean (Audit O-4).
#
# Everything listed here is excluded from the context sent to the daemon, which
# means smaller/faster builds and — importantly — a much lower chance of
# accidentally baking secrets, docs, or reference infra into an image layer.
# Only the Go module (source, go.mod, go.sum) actually needs to reach the build.

# Version control metadata — never needed inside an image.
.git
.gitignore

# Documentation and reference material — irrelevant to the compiled binary.
*.md
vps-docs/

# Build/deploy descriptors — these configure the host, not the image, and would
# otherwise invalidate the build cache on every infra edit.
Dockerfile
.dockerignore
docker-compose.yml
nginx.conf

# Locally compiled binaries — the image must ONLY ever contain the binary built
# hermetically inside the builder stage, never a stale host-built artifact.
# (Patterns are anchored to the context root, so cmd/server source is unaffected.)
server
mcp-server
bin/

# Local deploy ledgers (push_codebase audit logs) — never bake into an image.
deploy_ledgers/
